PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779981070
OL,3,CBurnham and Streeting hit back at Tony
OL,4,CBlair's criticism of Labour
OL,6,FStreeting noted that it was unclear
OL,7,Fwhether the 21st century would defined
OL,8,Fby "democracy or tyranny", but ended
OL,9,Fhis article by saying the future
OL,10,Fbelongs to "those prepared to harness
OL,11,Fchange in the service of justice".
OL,13,FBlair had praised both Burnham and
OL,14,FStreeting in his essay, in which he
OL,15,Fwas also critical of the government's
OL,16,Fspending on welfare and called for the
OL,17,Ftriple lock on pensions to be reformed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
